{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567086","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567086"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:54:29+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:54:29+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18931"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18931","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18931"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.02,0.91,0.02,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11665"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80344"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11665","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11665"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18931"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65613"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"2425"},{"type":"tags","id":"4986"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4989"},{"type":"tags","id":"4990"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5669"},{"type":"tags","id":"5671"},{"type":"tags","id":"5678"},{"type":"tags","id":"7823"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11286"},{"type":"tags","id":"11350"},{"type":"tags","id":"11645"},{"type":"tags","id":"11648"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27449"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27455"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35223"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45087"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80344","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80344"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA General Practitioner is considering implementing an artificial intelligence (AI) scribing tool to automatically generate clinical notes during patient consultations. The tool uses generative AI technology and requires audio recording of the consultation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the appropriate approach to implementing this AI tool?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Add a mandatory consent checkbox to online booking forms","Display a general notice in the waiting room about AI use","Obtain informed consent and document it in patient records before use","Inform patients after the consultation that AI was used for note-taking","Implement the tool without informing patients as it is only for administrative purposes"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eobtain informed consent and document it in patient records before use\u003C/strong\u003E. This is essential because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe AI tool processes personal patient information\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe consultation is being recorded\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThere may be legal implications if consent is not obtained\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EPatient data may become public domain if using public generative AI\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are problematic because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdd a mandatory consent checkbox to online booking forms\u003C/strong\u003E - This does not allow for adequate explanation of the risks and benefits, and may not reach all patients\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDisplay a general notice in the waiting room\u003C/strong\u003E - This is insufficient for informed consent when processing personal information\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInform patients after the consultation\u003C/strong\u003E - Consent must be obtained before recording or processing personal information\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImplement the tool without informing patients\u003C/strong\u003E - This violates patient autonomy and privacy rights\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare practitioners have an ethical and legal obligation to protect patient privacy and obtain explicit consent when using AI tools that process personal information.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Healthcare practitioners must obtain informed consent before using AI tools that process personal patient data, including AI scribing tools.","Using public generative AI tools for patient consultations risks making personal information public domain and requires explicit patient consent.","Documentation of patient consent for AI use should be recorded in the health record."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. New guidance on using AI in healthcare [internet]. 2024 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available from: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/News/Newsletters/September-2024.aspx#AI"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65613"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18931"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65613","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65613"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-20T14:17:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-20T14:18:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11665"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80344"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"ta